<h2 id="get-started">How to Get Started with Sonic Fan Games</h2>
<p>Every sonic fan game featured on this site is <strong>completely free to download and play</strong>. No catches, no subscriptions, no hidden costs. These are passion projects made by fans, for fans.</p>
<p>Most games run on <strong>Windows</strong>, and several also support <strong>Android</strong>. A few projects built in Dreams are available on <strong>PS4 and PS5</strong>. You do not need a powerful PC for the majority of them — many run on modest hardware since they are built with accessibility in mind.</p>
<p>If you are new and wondering where to start, here are four recommendations that cover different styles:</p>
<ol>
<li><strong><a href="/sonic-triple-trouble-16-bit/">Sonic Triple Trouble 16-bit</a></strong> — The perfect entry point for classic Sonic fans. Polished, complete, and feels like an official game.</li>
<li><strong><a href="/robo-blast-2/">Sonic Robo Blast 2</a></strong> — The best 3D Sonic fan game, with endless content and mods to keep you going.</li>
<li><strong><a href="/3-air/">Sonic 3 A.I.R.</a></strong> — If you want to replay a classic, this is the ultimate version of Sonic 3 &amp; Knuckles.</li>
<li><strong><a href="/smackdown/">Sonic Smackdown</a></strong> — Something completely different: a legit fighting game with Sonic characters.</li>
</ol>
<p>Every game on this site has its own dedicated page with screenshots, details, and a direct download link. Pick one that catches your eye and jump in — you might be surprised at how good these fan-made sonic games really are.</p>

